PUH-BrianMartell Zitterbewegung from Chiral Knot Jitter  Understandable Explanation Zitterbewegung (trembling motion) is the rapid oscillation of free Dirac particles around their average path at light speed  a direct consequence of the Dirac equation mixing positive/negative energy solutions. In PUH v25, it emerges naturally from chiral knot dynamics:   Knot = chiral soliton with handed twist.   In lattice, knot center-of-mass moves while internal twist precesses (jitter from discrete node interactions).   Relativistic motion: Positive/negative frequency components interfere  trembling at c.   No mystery  mechanical jitter of chiral topology in discrete substrate. Bosons (integer spin) lack this handedness conflict  smooth propagation.
